<task id="AIPU2-104" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Adapt existing WizardDialog components for embedded Workspace rendering</title>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <tags>frontend, wizards, workspace</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-077</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    The existing WizardDialog components (CreateMatterWizard, DocumentUploadWizard,
    SearchSelectDialog) currently render as modal overlays. In the three-pane layout,
    wizards should be embeddable directly as WorkspaceWidgets so users can complete
    multi-step workflows without losing their document or chat context. The chat in
    ConversationPane should be able to drive wizard step progression via PaneEventBus
    events (e.g. "set the matter name to..."), and the Context pane should show
    relevant information for the current wizard step. ADR-012 applies: shared components
    from @spaarke/ui-components must be reused.
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with familiarity with the shared WizardDialog component library and WorkspaceWidget patterns.</role>
  <goal>
    CreateMatterWizard, DocumentUploadWizard, and SearchSelectDialog can render as
    WorkspaceWidgets (embedded in workspace tabs) in addition to their existing modal mode.
    Chat can advance wizard steps via PaneEventBus WizardStepEvent. The Context pane shows
    step-relevant help or data during the wizard flow.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/Wizard</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/WorkspacePane</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Audit CreateMatterWizard, DocumentUploadWizard, and SearchSelectDialog in the shared component library. Identify what props/state need to be extracted to make them embeddable (remove modal chrome, expose step control externally).</step>
    <step>Add an embeddable prop to each wizard component. When true: render without Dialog wrapper, expose onStepChange callback, expose currentStep and totalSteps as controlled props.</step>
    <step>Create WorkspaceWidgetWizard wrapper: implements WorkspaceWidget interface, renders the wizard in embedded mode, serializes step progress for session restore.</step>
    <step>Define WizardStepEvent on PaneEventBus: { type: 'wizard-step', wizardId: string, action: 'next' | 'back' | 'set-field', fieldName?: string, fieldValue?: unknown }. ConversationPane can dispatch this when the AI suggests advancing a step.</step>
    <step>In WorkspaceWidgetWizard, subscribe to WizardStepEvent and apply the action to the wizard state (advance step, set field value).</step>
    <step>On wizard step change, dispatch TabChangedEvent (from AIPU2-103) with step metadata so ContextPaneController can show step-relevant context (e.g. required fields, help text).</step>
    <step>Define context widget mappings for each wizard step type in ContextPaneController's contextWidgetMap.</step>
    <step>Verify existing modal behavior is unchanged when embeddable prop is false — no regression on existing wizard usage.</step>
    <step>Test: open DocumentUploadWizard as a workspace tab, have chat send a WizardStepEvent to advance to step 2, verify Context pane updates to show step 2 help.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>CreateMatterWizard, DocumentUploadWizard, and SearchSelectDialog render correctly as WorkspaceWidgets (embedded, no modal chrome).</criterion>
    <criterion>WizardStepEvent dispatched from ConversationPane advances the wizard to the correct step.</criterion>
    <criterion>Wizard field values can be set programmatically via WizardStepEvent set-field action.</criterion>
    <criterion>Context pane updates to show step-relevant information on each step change.</criterion>
    <criterion>Wizard step progress is included in WorkspaceWidget serialized state for session restore.</criterion>
    <criterion>Existing modal usage of all three wizards is unchanged (no regression).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
